[100.432458, "o", "# TD-001: Temperature Conversion - Technical Design\r\n\r\n**Relates to:** FEAT-001  \r\n**Status:** Design  \r\n**Date:** 2026-04-05\r\n\r\n## Architecture Overview\r\n\r\nSingle entry point at `bin/convert.js` implementing a lightweight command-line temperature converter. No external dependencies; pure Node.js implementation using native JavaScript arithmetic.\r\n\r\n## Module Structure\r\n\r\n### File: `bin/convert.js`\r\n\r\n**Exports:**\r\n"]
[100.432488, "o", "\r\n- `toFahrenheit(celsius)` вЂ” Converts Celsius to Fahrenheit\r\n  - Formula: `(c * 9/5) + 32`\r\n  - Returns: Number formatted to one decimal place\r\n  \r\n"]
[100.432692, "o", "...\r\n\r\n"]
